<br>
I said yes, and we decided that we would get our mains (51 sj, 56 shaman) to loot the hearts and rod of bone, then give the wizards the lambent stones and MQ them for each others.. Well, all went well, the rod of bone and heart of frost were easy, totaling only abaut three hours..<br>
<br>
But then came the, quite literally, hellish part, SolA. We wasted five hours in the dungeon, killing endless amounts of goblins, seeing a wizard perhaps every 30 minutes or so, if even that often. Result was, two frustrated people, five hours lost, no hearts, /ooc'd to no end. The day ended with my friend falling in the lava and in an interesting CR.<br>
<br>
So, here's where I am. My wizard has the Staff of ro, my shaman the heart of frost and rod of bone. If I can get the heart of fire for my shaman, can I hand them to Gardern, and then get wizard to hand him the staff of ro? They are both on the same account.<br>
<br>
If I ever get out of there, I will never ever step a foot in SolA again.<br>
<br>
-Rotbone Binkbonk, 56th level Oger shaman<br>
-Cendywen, 28th level high elf wizard<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utaarne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taarne</A> at: 9/28/02 1:43:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Blueberry Nuker</span><br>  Posts: 1083<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/02 7:33 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MQing SoTF?</span><hr size=1> Yes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhibashira.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/02 2:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MQing SoTF?</span><hr size=1> Park both of them there before the turn in so you can switch quickly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujago668.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jago668</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/30/02 9:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MQing SoTF?</span><hr size=1> Aye.  I mq'd it last night with my 34 wizard.  Went and got everything with my 51 monk.  Gave the lambent stone to the wizard, wizard got staff.  Parked both right at Garden.  Monk turned in both hear